      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i've been watching the sparrows in my backyard for like three weeks now and something weird is happening. they aren't just flying around randomly. every time the wind shifts a certain way before a storm, they do this specific synchronized banking pattern towards the east. it's like they're communicating the pressure change before it even happens. i can actually tell when a rain front is coming just by watching their flight paths. do u think there's some kind of frequency or signal they're using that i'm picking up on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
